OL,7,FThe prisons overcrowding crisis is
OL,8,Fdown to the failure by the previous
OL,9,FConservative government to make sure
OL,10,Fpolicy changes bringing in longer jail
OL,11,Fsentences and boosting police numbers
OL,12,Fmatched the space available in prisons
OL,13,Fto hold criminals, according to a
OL,14,Freport published on Wednesday.
OL,16,FCampaigners branded the findings
OL,17,F"damning" and the spiralling costs
OL,18,F"eye-watering" as they repeated calls
OL,19,Ffor an overhaul of how criminals are
OL,20,Fsentenced.
