OL,7,FSir Geoffrey Clifton-Brown, chairman
OL,8,Fof the Commons Public Accounts
OL,9,FCommittee which scrutinises government
OL,10,Fspending, said prisons were "already
OL,11,Fat the brink" and it was
OL,12,F"unacceptable" that plans "beset with
OL,13,Fdelays" would not meet future demand.
OL,15,F"The Ministry of Justice (MoJ) has
OL,16,Fbeen in firefighting mode,
OL,17,Fprioritising short-term solutions to
OL,18,Fthe crisis. These are not only
OL,19,Fexpensive but also increase risks to
OL,20,Fprisoner, staff and public safety.
